HOLY CANNOLI HERE SHE IS üí´üçãüíõüß° the BEAUTIFUL sunny front cover of my FIRST EVER cookbook, Bittery Honey. So named because let‚Äôs face it, life (like food) can be both bitter and sweet, and that‚Äôs really  what makes it so fascinating. To say this book has been a labour of love is an enormous understatement - 3 years in the making and packed with recipes to truly relish and capture the spirit of this extraordinary place where I found myself three years ago. It‚Äôs so much more than just a book of recipes: it‚Äôs a love letter to this island and to the simple joys of Italian food. I have wanted to write a cookbook my whole life so this is really the realisation of a dream, and I am grateful to all of you who helped make it happen, you all know you are (I hope!!) but I‚Äôm gunna tag as many of you as I can anyway. What a bloody great day it is. Order now see link in profile and get yourself a slice of Sardinian sunshine on this grey Monday morning.
